{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Only better foundation models like Mistral, Starling and Yi can provide the means for a performance boost to a completely new level.",
    "Comparison of own test results with popular benchmarks like MMLU, MT-Bench and GSM8K show, that models seem to be optimized for certain type of questions.",
    "Starling 7B e.g.",
    "outperforms all other 7B and even larger open source models on MT-Bench and MMLU, whereas in our tests it does not reach the performance of Dolphin Mistral 7B or Neural Chat 7B.",
    "This is partly due to bad performance on trick questions, but also due to symbolic reasoning.Instruction-tuning and DPO provide a much better training resulting in models giving substantially better answers than models without this kind of finetuning as stated in literature [28], [37], [44], [54]."
  ],
